EXTENDED
DATA REPORT

The personalized extended data report of your Lipotype-analyzed dataset. This html document presents the plots and excel sheets from the included "Data" folder, which can itself be accessed separately. For an even more interactive representation of the results, please use Lipotype Zoom.

LIPID CLASSES

All individual measurements of lipid species within one class are summed to a class profile. Bars represent cohort means. Error bars correspond to standard deviation. Data are reported in either raw pmol values (pmol) or as normalized to the total sample amount (mol%).

ALL DATA

  • Class profile in pmol

    XLSX
  • Class profile in mol%sample
    PDF
    XLSX

SPECIES PROFILES

Lipid species or subspecies are plotted within this section for every lipid class. Bars represent cohort means. Error bars correspond to standard deviation. Data are reported in either raw pmol values (pmol) or as normalized to the total sample amount (mol%).

LIPID FEATURES

Features are:
- Carbon length profiles (with prefix “C”)
- Double bond profiles (with prefix “DB”)
- Hydroxylation profiles (with prefix “OH”)
All features are standardised to mol% of the lipid class. Bars represent cohort means. Error bars correspond to standard deviation.

ALL DATA (EXCEL)

  • All features (pmol%class)
    XLSX

PRINCIPAL COMPONENT ANALYSIS

WITH PMOL DATA

Pmol data are displayed here as a principal component analysis (PCA). The score plot shows the individual replicates (shortnames) clusters colored by cohort. This view is used to assess the overall separation of the cohorts taking into account the spread between and within the cohorts. Conversely, the loadings plot shows each lipid and is used to visually assess which lipid features contribute highly to the separation of cohorts. Finally, the total amount of variation within your data explained by each principal component is shown in the variability plot.

ALL DATA (EXCEL)

  • All data (pmol)
    XLSX

PLOTS (PDF)

  • Score Plot
    PDF
  • Loadings Plot
    PDF
  • Variability Plot

PRINCIPAL COMPONENT ANALYSIS

WITH MOL% DATA

Mol% data are displayed here as a principal component analysis (PCA). The score plot shows the individual replicates (shortnames) clusters colored by cohort. This view is used to assess the overall separation of the cohorts taking into account the spread between and within the cohorts. Conversely, the loadings plot shows each lipid and is used to visually assess which lipid features contribute highly to the separation of cohorts. Finally, the total amount of variation within your data explained by each principal component is shown in the variability plot.
